        <headline>Flood Advisory issued August 5 at 5:17PM EDT until August 5 at 6:30PM EDT by NWS Charleston SC</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall is expected.

* WHERE...A portion of southeast South Carolina, including the
following counties, Allendale, Colleton and Hampton.

* WHEN...Until 630 PM EDT.

* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 516 PM EDT, Doppler radar indicated thunderstorms with
torrential rainfall extending from Jenny south to Gifford. A
quick 1 to 3 inches of rain could fall through 630 PM,
resulting in minor flooding of low-lying and poor drainage
areas.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Hampton, Lake Warren State Park, Varnville, Fairfax, Brunson,
Gifford, Sycamore, Luray, Lodge and Ulmer.
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.</instruction>
